🌐 Day 05 — Linux Networking Basics

Networking is one of the most important skills in DevOps.
Today we will learn how Linux systems communicate with servers, websites, and networks.

📌 Why Networking Matters in DevOps?

DevOps Engineers work with:

☁️ Cloud servers
🌐 APIs
🐳 Docker containers
☸️ Kubernetes clusters
🔄 CI/CD pipelines

To troubleshoot infrastructure, networking knowledge is essential.

🌍 1. ping — Check Network Connectivity
📌 Definition

ping checks whether a server or website is reachable.

It sends packets to the target system and waits for a response.

🛠️ Syntax
ping website_or_ip
✅ Example
ping google.com
✅ Example Output
64 bytes from google.com: icmp_seq=1 ttl=117 time=20 ms
🔴 Stop Ping

Press:

CTRL + C

🌐 2. ifconfig — Network Interface Information
📌 Definition

Displays:

IP address
Network interface details
MAC address
🛠️ Syntax
ifconfig
⚠️ Note

Modern Linux systems may not have ifconfig installed by default.

Install it using:

sudo apt install net-tools

🌐 3. ip — Modern Network Command
📌 Definition

ip is the modern replacement for ifconfig.

Used for:

Viewing IP addresses
Network interfaces
Routing information
🛠️ Syntax
ip a
✅ Example Output
inet 192.168.1.10/24

🌍 4. hostname -I — Get System IP Address
📌 Definition

Displays system IP address.

🛠️ Syntax
hostname -I
✅ Example Output
192.168.1.10

🔌 5. netstat — Network Statistics
📌 Definition

Displays:

Open ports
Active connections
Listening services
🛠️ Syntax
netstat -tulnp
📖 Option Meaning
Option	Meaning
-t	TCP connections
-u	UDP connections
-l	Listening ports
-n	Numeric output
-p	Process information
✅ Example Output
tcp   0   0 0.0.0.0:22   LISTEN

📡 Port 22 is open for SSH.

⚠️ Install netstat
sudo apt install net-tools

⚡ 6. ss — Socket Statistics
📌 Definition

Modern replacement for netstat.

Faster and more efficient.

🛠️ Syntax
ss -tulnp

🌐 7. curl — Transfer Data from URLs
📌 Definition

Used to:

Access APIs
Download webpage content
Test endpoints

Very important in DevOps.

🛠️ Syntax
curl URL
✅ Example
curl https://google.com
🔥 Real DevOps Example

Check public IP:

curl ifconfig.me

📥 8. wget — Download Files
📌 Definition

Downloads files directly from internet.

🛠️ Syntax
wget file_url
✅ Example
wget https://example.com/file.zip
📂 Verify Download
ls
🧪 Hands-On Practice

Run these commands:

ping google.com

ip a

hostname -I

ss -tulnp

curl ifconfig.me

🔥 Real DevOps Scenario
Check if Nginx Server is Running
ss -tulnp

Look for:

:80

✅ Means web server is running.

🌍 Test Website Response
curl http://localhost
📦 Download File from Internet
wget https://example.com/sample.zip

🎯 Important Commands Summary
Command	Purpose
ping	Check connectivity
ifconfig	Network details
ip a	Show IP address
hostname -I	System IP
netstat	Network statistics
ss	Open ports
curl	Access URLs/APIs
wget	Download files

💡 Key Learnings

✅ Networking is critical in DevOps
✅ ping checks server connectivity
✅ ip a shows IP configuration
✅ ss checks listening ports
✅ curl is widely used for APIs
✅ wget downloads files from internet
